post_text: On Sept. 15, Seguin ISD - Home of the Matadors was awarded the High Demand Job Training Grant from the Texas Workforce Commission and the Seguin Economic Development Corporation Corporation. The total amount awarded from both parties was $17,324.72 with $10,438.95 coming straight from the Seguin Economic Development Corporation.

post_text: Hispanic Heritage Month recognizes and celebrates the contributions Americans tracing their roots to Spain, Mexico, Central America, South American and the Spanish-speaking nations of the Caribbean have made to American society and culture. The observance was born in 1968 when Congress authorized the president to issue an annual proclamation designating National Hispanic Heritage Week. Just two decades later, lawmakers expanded it to a monthlong celebration, stretching from September 15 to October 15. #TeamSeguin

post_text: Germs are everywhere! They can get onto our hands and items we touch during daily activities and make us sick. Cleaning hands at key times with soap and water or hand sanitizer that contains at least 60% alcohol is one of the most important steps you can take to avoid getting sick and spreading germs to those around you. Watch Dr. Al from Alligator Dental as he shares some awesome advice about keeping germs away. #SeguinStrong

post_text:
Seguin ISD offers two online registration services for parents. Parents of returning students will login with their SchoolMint account and update / change their student information. Parents of new students will create a SchoolMint account and complete full enrollment information.

What is New Student vs Returning Student?

A New Student is any student that was not enrolled at Seguin ISD on the last day of school for the 19 - 20 school year. This includes students who may have been enrolled the year prior or attended Seguin ISD before.

A Returning Student is any student that was enrolled in a Seguin ISD school on the last day of school during the 2019-2020 school year. If you have another child that is a new student you can add them through your returning students account.

Online registration is open now! It's easy to get started--select an option below.

New student: https://www.seguin.k12.tx.us/page/rr.new
Returning student: https://www.seguin.k12.tx.us/page/rr.returning

Questions? Please contact your child's school.

A message from Dr. Gutierrez:

The last day that meals will be served through the Seguin ISD Summer Meal program is today, Thursday, Aug. 27. Today, breakfast and lunch meals will be provided through Monday, Aug. 31.

Seguin ISD families, thank you for trusting the district to provide over 300,000 meals to the children of Seguin over the course of 150-plus days since March.

I truly appreciate the hard work and dedication of the Child Nutrition, Transportation, and Custodial staffs to provide meals during the closure and over the course of the summer months. Rain nor 100 degree heat while wearing masks deterred our employees from serving our students. I am grateful to have selfless individuals working for Seguin ISD.

Seguin ISD offers two online registration services for parents. Parents of returning students will login with their SchoolMint account and update / change their student information. Parents of new students will create a SchoolMint account and complete full enrollment information.

What is New Student vs Returning Student?

A New Student is any student that was not enrolled at Seguin ISD on the last day of school for the 19 - 20 school year. This includes students who may have been enrolled the year prior or attended Seguin ISD before.

A Returning Student is any student that was enrolled in a Seguin ISD school on the last day of school during the 2019-2020 school year. If you have another child that is a new student you can add them through your returning students account.

Online registration is open now! It's easy to get started--select an option below.

New student:
Returning student: https://www.seguin.k12.tx.us/page/rr.returning

Questions? Please contact your child's school.

post_text:
A physical is required for all incoming 7th grade students who want to participate in athletics as well as any athlete who has never had one on file with Seguin ISD.

Any 8-12 grade student-athlete with a current physical on file will need to complete the Medical History Form before participating. If questions 1-6 of the form are marked "yes" then the student must have a new physical.

Physicals will be offered for $25 at Seguin High School on Aug. 26 from 5:30-7 p.m. Please enter the middle set of doors at the Seguin ISD Athletics Department on the south end of Seguin High School.

To adhere to the safety guidelines, we are asking that only the student-athlete and one parent enter the facility. Everyone must wear a mask and will be screened upon entry. If you do not feel well please do attend.

To download forms go to https://bit.ly/2WiLrM8

Seguin ISD parents,

As we prepare to welcome students back for the Sept. 8 first day of school, we have created a document designed to address learning options, health and safety, student meals and transportation. It is our hope that the Back to School Blueprint will serve as a useful reference tool for you. Please keep in mind that this is a fluid document and over the next few weeks we will update it as local, state and national guidelines change.

The document will reside at www.seguinisd.net and will be re-posted as it is updated.

Thank you for your continued patience and flexibility. We look forward to serving our students this fall.

Dr. Matthew Gutierrez
Seguin ISD Superintendent

Sales Tax Holiday
During the COVID-19 pandemic, the Comptroller encourages all taxpayers to continue practicing social distancing and support Texas businesses while saving money on tax-free purchases of most clothing, footwear, school supplies and backpacks (sold for less than $100) during the annual Tax-Free weekend. Qualifying items can be purchased tax free from a Texas store or from an online or catalog seller doing business in Texas. In most cases, you do not need to give the seller an exemption certificate to buy qualifying items tax free.

This year‚Äôs sales tax holiday begins Friday, Aug. 7, and goes through midnight Sunday, Aug. 9. Froe more information go to https://bit.ly/3a2PGRv

A physical is required for all incoming 7th grade students who want to participate in athletics as well as any athlete who has never had one on file with Seguin ISD.

Any 8-12 grade student-athlete with a current physical on file will need to complete the Medical History Form before participating. If questions 1-6 of the form are marked "yes" then the student must have a new physical.

Physicals will be offered for $25 at Seguin High School on July 22 and Aug. 5 from 5:30-7 p.m. Please enter the middle set of doors at the Seguin ISD Athletics Department on the south end of Seguin High School.

To adhere to the safety guidelines, we are asking that only the student-athlete and one parent enter the facility. Everyone must wear a mask and will be screened upon entry. If you do not feel well please do attend.

To download forms go to https://bit.ly/2WiLrM8

post_text:
Message from Dr. Gutierrez
As anticipated, charter networks, especially virtual, are seizing on the pandemic as an opportunity to take additional dollars from local ISDs by actively recruiting public school students.

Don‚Äôt fall into the trap. Local school districts will be able to meet the needs of the students they serve, and they are locally based and governed. In addition, local ISDs have deep rooted connections and partnerships with their families and greater communities.

Seguin ISD is eager and ready to provide remote/virtual learning to the students in our very own community.

The Children‚Äôs Grief Program of Hope Hospice will be hosting a grief camp for children this summer in Seguin! Camp HavenHeart Seguin will be held June 29-July 2 from 9 am to 3 pm daily at The Seguin Outdoor Learning Center. This camp is for children ages 7-16 who have experienced the death of a loved one. There is no cost to attend.

The registration deadline for this camp is June 19, 2020. A screening interview is required for each child participating and campers are accepted on a first-come, first-served basis after it is determined that they are emotionally ready to participate in and benefit from the camp. Children must be able to attend all of camp; no partial attendance.

post_text:
Congratulations to Suzanne Zink - SHS Administrative Intern

Suzanne Zink received her Bachelor of Science with a Major in Dance Education from Texas State University and is currently working on a Master in Educational Administration from Texas A&M San Antonio. Ms. Zink has spent her 11-year career with Seguin ISD where she has taught Cheerleading, Dance, and Physical Education at Seguin High School. She developed and implemented the Sparkles Cheerleading Program and has been the Head Cheerleading Coach for the past 10 years, being awarded the 5A-D1 Texas Cheerleading Coach of the Year in 2016-2017. In addition, Ms. Zink has served on the Seguin ISD Safety and Security Committee and the SHS Site-Based Decision Management Committee. She looks forward to continuing her career with Seguin ISD. Go Matadors! #MatadorPride

Beginning Friday, April 3, we will serve meals for Fridays, Saturdays, and Sundays during our Friday lunch meal service. With this change, we will:
Remove Saturday meal service.
Provide six meals on Fridays during our lunch meal service (three breakfasts and three lunches) to cover student meals for Fridays, Saturdays, and Sundays.
Campus and bus delivery Grab & Go meal locations will not change. Campus locations are Ball Early Childhood Center, Jefferson, Koennecke, McQueeney, Patlan and Rodriguez elementaries, plus Seguin High School.
Bus delivery locations are
‚Ä¢ 1055 E US 90 (Kingsbury Post Office)
‚Ä¢ 200 block of Country Acres (at mailboxes)
‚Ä¢ 100 block of Parkcreek at Creekway (in Parkcreek)
‚Ä¢ 146 Sandy Oaks Dr. (VFD)
‚Ä¢ FM 725 & Grove Ln. (McQueeney)
‚Ä¢ 275 Gallagher Rd. (VFW building in McQueeney Estates)
‚Ä¢ 8251 FM 1117 (Forest Hills Baptist Church)
‚Ä¢ 9071 FM 467 (Olmos Store)

Thank you for your continued patience as we strive to support our Seguin ISD students and families.

Beginning today (March 30), breakfast will be served with lunch each day during the lunch meal service from 11:30 a.m. to 1 p.m. Mondays through Thursdays. With this change, we will:

Remove the breakfast service time of 7:30-8:30 a.m.

Serve two meals (one breakfast and one lunch) during our lunch meal service from 11:30 a.m. to 1 p.m.

Help reduce parent, student and staff risk of exposure by interacting once per day.

Beginning Friday, April 3, we will serve meals for Fridays, Saturdays, and Sundays during our Friday lunch meal service. With this change, we will:

Remove the Saturday meal service.

post_text: Breanna Lind (Matador class of 2012) is a Chicago-based actor. She graduated from The University of Texas at Austin with a B.A. in Theatre and Dance in 2016 and moved to Chicago to pursue her career as an actor. During her time at Seguin High School, Breanna was involved with the SHS Drama Club, Varsity Choir, Guadalupe County 4H, and StuCo where she served as Class President all four years with her best friend and partner in crime, Brianna Reinhard. You may recognize Breanna from when her favorite teacher and biggest inspiration, Sheila Lucas, cast her as the 'Back End of the Cow' in Jack and the Beanstalk her freshman year and thrust her into a life of theatre! If you're ever in Chicago, you can find Breanna performing improvisational comedy weekly at the iO Theater with her team, Crocodile Nasties. You can also catch her this summer in Nia DaCosta/Jordan Peele's Candyman (or right now, she's in the trailer!). She loves Seguin and brings up her hometown any chance she gets. Go Mats Go!

post_text:
This summer, Seguin ISD parents will register students online for the 2020-2021 school year. ‚ÄúWe believe this process will greatly benefit our parents and guardians by allowing them to enroll their children quickly and at their leisure. Online registration will keep parents from having to stand in line and fill out multiple paper forms,‚Äù said Dr. Matthew Gutierrez, superintendent.
Online registration will be mandatory for all returning and new students to Seguin ISD for the fall.
‚ÄúWith this new, automated process the back-to-school time should be easier for our families,‚Äù he added.
The online system should be live when registration begins in July. Once finalized, the district will provide parents with instructions for creating accounts, tutorials on how to register, timelines for registering, and support options. This information will be shared
on district social media outlets and at www.seguinisd.net as well.

The Texas University Scholastic League (UIL) released realignments for 2020-2021 and 2021-2022 and as a result, Seguin High School will have new competition.

In football, Class 5A Division 1 District 12 will include Seguin, San Antonio Veterans Memorial, Harlandale, McCollum, New Braunfels Canyon, Buda Johnson, Dripping Springs and Kyle Lehman.

Basketball and volleyball teams competing in District 26-5A will include Seguin, Boerne Champion, Buda Johnson, New Braunfels Canyon, Dripping Springs, Kerrville Tivy, Kyle Lehman, Alamo Heights and San Antonio Veterans Memorial.

For view complete lists of high school realignments, visit https://buff.ly/37WG0WH.

post_text: Seguin High School Matador Theatre is proud to present the Disney sensation, Beauty and the Beast, as the 2020 winter musical. The students look forward to bringing the famous music and characters of the original Disney film to the Performing Arts Center stage. This show will thrill and delight audiences of all ages. Showtimes are Friday, Jan. 24 and Saturday, Jan. 25 at 7 p.m. and Sunday, Jan. 26 at 3 p.m. Tickets are available at Keepers and Gift and Gourmet, as well as at the door. The price is $12 pre-sale / $15 door for adults and $8 pre-sale / $10 door for students. Season tickets are also available at these vendors for $45 and include the 2020 musical and one act play, preferential seating and parking, and two complimentary concessions per show. Please call Kelly for more information at 830-305-1534.

post_text: Mychelle Renee Orichuela, daughter of Michael and Ruby Orichuela, attended Koennecke Elementary School, Jim Barnes Middle School and a Seguin High School Matador graduate in 2016. Mychelle graduated on December 15, 2019, Cum Laude from UTSA - The University of Texas at San Antonio with her Bachelor's degree in Psychology and Minor in Sociology. Congratulations Mychelle! #MatadorPride

post_text: Congratulations to Ashley Littlefield, Matador graduate class of 2015, and her parents Sidney and Michele Littlefield! Ashley attended McQueeney Elementary and Briesemeister Middle School. She graduated from Texas State University on December 14, 2019, with a Bachelor of Business Administration in finance and management and has already started her career at McCoy's Building Supply's corporate office as a pricing analyst. #TeamSeguin
